body:
@vivostar 
The cause seems to be pinning the version of puppetlabs-stdlib is insufficient in [bigtop_toolchain::puppet_modules](https://github.com/apache/bigtop/blob/master/bigtop_toolchain/manifests/puppet_modules.pp). You should fix the manifest rather than README.md.

Since the puppetize.sh belonging to bigtop_toolchain covers installation of Puppet itself, the README of puppet-deploy does not assume to use it. [bigtop_toolchain::puppet_modules](https://github.com/apache/bigtop/blob/master/bigtop_toolchain/manifests/puppet_modules.pp) is the class for installing only puppetlabs-stdlib to the environment in which puppet is already installed.

@cheelio Great improvement, thank you for the contribution!
Just a quick question, is there any handy way to check if IDs defined in the repos variable covers all repositories used by the Bigtop components?
I'm worried that if some components change their repository definition with their upgrade, or are added/removed with their repo definition, we are likely to forget to update the value of the repos variable.
